M|milestone|Create the file `.tmp/milestones/issue-{N}-milestone-{M}.md`:
M|milestone|```markdown
M|milestone|**Branch:** issue-{N}
M|milestone|**Created:** {current-datetime}
M|milestone|**LOC Implemented:** ~{cumulative_loc} lines
M|milestone|**Test Status:** {passed}/{total} tests passed
M|milestone|[Work Remaining section from Step 2]
M|milestone|[Next File Changes section from Step 3]
M|milestone|[Test Status section from Step 4]
M|milestone|```
M|milestone|**CRITICAL: Local-Only Checkpoint Files**
M|milestone|Milestone documents in `.tmp/milestones/` are LOCAL CHECKPOINT FILES ONLY:
M|milestone|- **DO NOT** stage these files: `git add .tmp/milestones/` is FORBIDDEN
M|milestone|- **DO NOT** force-add these files: `git add -f .tmp/milestones/*` is FORBIDDEN
M|milestone|- **DO NOT** commit these files under any circumstances
M|milestone|- These files are automatically excluded by `.gitignore` when using `git add .`
M|milestone|**Why `.tmp/milestones/` files must remain local:**
M|milestone|1. They are working notes for resuming implementation between sessions
M|milestone|2. They contain partial progress states not suitable for repository history
M|milestone|3. `.gitignore` already excludes them to prevent accidental staging
M|milestone|4. Only completed implementation code/tests/docs should be committed
M|milestone|**Verification:** Before creating any commit, verify staged files:
M|milestone|```bash
M|milestone|git diff --cached --name-only
M|milestone|```
M|milestone|If you see any `.tmp/milestones/` files listed, **STOP** and unstage them:
M|milestone|```bash
M|milestone|git restore --staged .tmp/milestones/
M|milestone|```
M|milestone|Use the `commit-msg` skill with milestone flag:
M|milestone|**CRITICAL - Pre-Commit Verification:**
M|milestone|Before invoking `commit-msg`, verify what will be staged:
M|milestone|```bash
M|milestone|git add .
M|milestone|git diff --cached --name-only
M|milestone|```
M|milestone|**Requirements:**
M|milestone|- **MUST stage**: Implementation code, tests, documentation
M|milestone|- **MUST NOT stage**: `.tmp/milestones/issue-{N}-milestone-{M}.md` (local checkpoint only)
M|milestone|- If `.tmp/milestones/` files appear in `git diff --cached`, unstage them immediately:
M|milestone|```bash
M|milestone|git restore --staged .tmp/milestones/
M|milestone|```
M|milestone|**Invoke commit-msg skill with:**
M|milestone|- Purpose: milestone
M|milestone|- Staged files: all implementation changes (code, tests, documentation)
M|milestone|- EXCLUDE: `.tmp/milestones/issue-{N}-milestone-{M}.md` (keep this local only)
M|milestone|- Issue number: {N}
M|milestone|- Test status: "{passed}/{total} tests passed"
M|milestone|The commit-msg skill will:
M|milestone|- Create commit message with `[milestone][tag]` prefix
M|milestone|- Include test status in message
M|milestone|- Use `git commit --no-verify` to bypass pre-commit hooks
M|milestone|- Reference the issue number
M|milestone|**Example commit message:**
M|milestone|```
M|milestone|[milestone][agt.skill]: Milestone 2 for issue #42
M|milestone|.claude/skills/milestone/SKILL.md: Implement LOC tracking and test parsing logic
M|milestone|docs/milestone-workflow.md: Add workflow documentation
M|milestone|Milestone progress: 820 LOC implemented, 5/8 tests passed.
M|milestone|Tests failing: edge case handling, integration tests.
M|milestone|NOTE: Milestone doc (.tmp/milestones/issue-42-milestone-2.md) is NOT committed - it remains local for resumption.
M|milestone|```
M|milestone|Display message to user:
M|milestone|```
M|milestone|Milestone {M} created at {cumulative_loc} LOC ({passed}/{total} tests passed).
M|milestone|Work remaining: ~{estimated_remaining_loc} LOC
M|milestone|```
M|milestone|**Next Steps:**
M|milestone|To resume implementation from this checkpoint, use natural language:
M|milestone|```
M|milestone|User: Resume from the latest milestone
M|milestone|User: Continue implementation
M|milestone|User: Continue from .tmp/milestones/issue-{N}-milestone-{M}.md
M|milestone|```
M|milestone|The system will auto-detect the latest milestone on the current branch.
M|milestone|When all tests pass (Condition A), signal completion:
M|milestone|```
M|milestone|All tests passed ({total}/{total})!
M|milestone|Implementation complete:
M|milestone|- Total LOC: ~{cumulative_loc}
M|milestone|- All {total} tests passing
M|milestone|Next steps:
M|milestone|1. Create a delivery commit (without [milestone] tag):
M|milestone|- Stage all changes: git add .
M|milestone|- Create commit with purpose=delivery (runs pre-commit hooks)
M|milestone|- All tests must pass for commit to succeed
M|milestone|2. rv and create PR with /pull-request --open
M|milestone|- Or use /code-rv then /open-pr for manual workflow
M|milestone|```
M|milestone|**CRITICAL - Completion requires a delivery commit:**
M|milestone|When all tests pass, **DO NOT create a milestone**. Instead:
M|milestone|1. **Stage changes for delivery commit:**
M|milestone|```bash
M|milestone|git add .
M|milestone|git diff --cached --name-only  # Verify staged files
M|milestone|```
M|milestone|2. **Create delivery commit using commit-msg skill:**
M|milestone|- Purpose: `delivery` (NOT milestone)
M|milestone|- No `--no-verify` flag (normal pre-commit hooks run)
M|milestone|- All tests must pass for commit to succeed
M|milestone|- Commit message has NO `[milestone]` tag
M|milestone|3. **Delivery commit distinguishes completed work from checkpoints:**
M|milestone|- Milestone commits = intermediate checkpoints with incomplete tests
M|milestone|- Delivery commits = completed work with all tests passing
M|milestone|- Only delivery commits should be merged to main branch
M|milestone|**Example delivery commit message:**
M|milestone|```
M|milestone|[feat][agt.command]: Add TypeScript support to build system
M|milestone|src/build.ts: Implement TypeScript compilation pl
M|milestone|tests/test-typescript.sh: Add TypeScript validation tests
M|milestone|All 8 tests passing. Ready for code rv.
M|milestone|```
M|milestone|```bash
M|milestone|git branch --show-current
M|milestone|```
M|milestone|If branch does not match pattern `issue-{N}` or `issue-{N}-*`:
M|milestone|```
M|milestone|Error: Not on a dev branch.
M|milestone|Current branch: {branch-name}
M|milestone|You must be on a dev branch (issue-{N}) to use the milestone skill.
M|milestone|Please run /issue-to-impl to start implementation on a proper dev branch.
M|milestone|```
M|milestone|Stop execution.
