M|milestone|```
M|milestone|Stop execution.
M|milestone|If tests fail to run due to syntax errors or import errors:
M|milestone|```bash
M|milestone|make test
M|milestone|```
M|milestone|Create milestone with error notes:
M|milestone|```markdown
M|milestone|**Critical Errors:**
M|milestone|- Syntax error in src/core.py:45
M|milestone|- Import error: module 'utils' not found
M|milestone|**Test Execution:** Failed to run tests due to critical errors.
M|milestone|**Next Steps:**
M|milestone|1. Fix syntax errors
M|milestone|2. Resolve import issues
M|milestone|3. Resume with /miles2miles
M|milestone|```
M|milestone|Then stop and inform user:
M|milestone|```
M|milestone|Critical errors detected. Milestone {M} created with error notes.
M|milestone|Errors:
M|milestone|- Syntax error in src/core.py:45
M|milestone|- Import error: module 'utils' not found
M|milestone|Please fix these errors and resume with: "Continue from the latest milestone"
M|milestone|```
M|milestone|If unable to create milestone file:
M|milestone|```
M|milestone|Error: Failed to create milestone file at .tmp/milestones/issue-{N}-milestone-{M}.md
M|milestone|Possible causes:
M|milestone|- .tmp/milestones/ directory does not exist
M|milestone|- Permission issues
M|milestone|Please ensure .tmp/milestones/ directory exists and is writable.
M|milestone|```
M|milestone|Try to create the directory:
M|milestone|```bash
M|milestone|mkdir -p .milestones
M|milestone|```
M|milestone|Then retry creating the milestone file.
M|milestone|If still fails, stop and report error to user.
